<br>
If you want this for your relationship .. your marriage, I can tell you you need to look for it in your own home.. your own relationship.  Dont look outside to try and fix your marriage excitment issues, work on them with your spouse.  <br>
<br>
Dont be overly pushy yet dont just let it go either.  You both have needs, and I can almost guarentee that if you feel this way he probably does also to some degree.  <br>
<br>
Work on your relationship and yes you can have excitment in your relationship even after many years.  <br>
<br>
It took a very tramatic experience for me to see this, but let me tell you after 13 years with my wife, It is feeling like our first few years again, it takes some work but it is definatly worth it.  Esp if you love your husband.<br>
<br>
talk with the other guy and let him know how you feel and that you would like to stop the *innocent fun* because it is making you feel uncomfortable.  Dont just stop seeing and talking to him otherwise he may double his efforts to get your attention.  If after explaining your situation to him if he keeps up with the flirting and stuff then you know exactly what it is he is after, then it becomes sexual harassment.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps you some.  <br>
